HEADWORD: Cenanthy
<hw>Ce*nan"thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ empty +
<?/ a flower.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The absence or suppression
of the essential organs (stamens and pistil) in a flower.</def>⟦br⟧
